The United States has strongly condemned the recent terrorist attack in Mogadishu, Somalia, which resulted in the death of over 50 people and injured more than 100. The attack is seen as an attempt by terrorists to undermine Somalia's progress towards a more representative government. The United States is standing with the people of Somalia during this crucial electoral period and expresses its condolences to the victims and their families. The US will continue to support Somalia and regional efforts to combat terrorism and extremism, as well as assist in the pursuit of a peaceful and inclusive future for Somalia.